parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description: The accelerated domain name. You can specify multiple accelerated domain names and separate them with commas (,).

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description:
The end of the time range to query.

The time follows the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time is displayed in UTC.

> The end time must be later than the start time.

parameters.name: Interval
parameters.description:
The time granularity for a query. Unit: seconds.

The time granularity varies with the maximum time range per query. Valid values: 300 (5 minutes), 3600 (1 hour), and 86400 (1 day). For more information, see **Usage notes**.

parameters.name: IspNameEn
parameters.description:
The name of the Internet service provider (ISP).

You can call the [DescribeDcdnRegionAndIsp](~~207199~~) operation to query ISPs.

parameters.name: LocationNameEn
parameters.description:
The name of the region.

You can call the [DescribeDcdnRegionAndIsp](~~207199~~) operation to query regions.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description:
The beginning of the time range to query.

The time follows the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time is displayed in UTC.
